          "Many German verbs require specific prepositions",
          "that don't translate literally to English:",
          "",
          "COMMON IDIOMS WITH 'AN':",
          "denken an (to think of/about)",
          "glauben an (to believe in)",
          "sich erinnern an (to remember)",
          "teilnehmen an (to participate in)",
          "",
          "Ich denke an dich. (I'm thinking of you)",
          "Er glaubt an Gott. (He believes in God)",
          "",
          "COMMON IDIOMS WITH 'AUF':",
          "warten auf (to wait for)",
          "hoffen auf (to hope for)",
          "sich freuen auf (to look forward to)",
          "ankommen auf (to depend on)",
          "",
          "Ich freue mich auf morgen!",
          "(I'm looking forward to tomorrow!)"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion 64"
